modules.description: Provides parallel versions of list and array transformations, including mapping, iterating, and folding with customizable thread initialization, finalization, and core pinning. Operates on lists and arrays, preserving input order for array operations. Enables parallel processing of large datasets with fine-grained control over execution environment.

Processes large files by dividing them into independent blocks using a demux function, then applies a computation to each block in parallel. Works with file data, custom block structures, and user-defined processing functions. Ideal for parallel log analysis, bulk data transformation, and large-scale text parsing.

Parallelizes list and array operations such as mapping, iterating, and folding, with control over thread lifecycle and core affinity. Processes large datasets efficiently while maintaining input order for array transformations. Supports custom initialization and finalization routines for each thread. Example tasks include parallel data filtering, aggregation, and transformation across multi-core systems.
